cious, intuition, memory, embodiment, and symbolization. By showing how the alluvial flood plains configure chaura life, Khan shows how nature can both give rise to and inhabit social, political, and spiritual forms of life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aHuman ecologyzBangladeshzJamuna River. 0aRiver settlementszBangladeshzJamuna River. 0aRural poorzBangladeshzJamuna River. 0aSand barszBangladeshzJamuna River. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478024002?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478024002423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478024002/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles